## 🗂️ GI Tract — Overview

| Segment                   | Embryological Origin                                     | Blood Supply                                                      | Length |
| ------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------- | ------ |
| [[Oral Cavity]]           | —                                                        | Facial / lingual arteries                                         | —      |
| [[Esophagus]]             | Foregut                                                  | Esophageal branches                                               | ~25 cm |
| [[Stomach]]               | Foregut                                                  | [[Celiac Trunk]] branches                                         | —      |
| [[Small Intestine]]       | Foregut (duodenum) / Midgut (jejunum, ileum)             | [[Celiac Trunk]] / SMA                                            | ~6 m   |
| [[Large Intestine]]       | Midgut (cecum–transverse) / Hindgut (descending–sigmoid) | SMA / IMA                                                         | ~1.5 m |
| [[Rectum and Anal Canal]] | Hindgut                                                  | Superior rectal (IMA) / Middle + inferior rectal (internal iliac) | ~15 cm |

## 🗂️ Accessory Organs

| Organ           | Function                                                     | Duct                                         |
| --------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------ | -------------------------------------------- |
| [[Liver]]       | Bile production, detoxification, metabolism                  | Bile ducts → common bile duct                |
| [[Gallbladder]] | Bile storage + concentration                                 | Cystic duct → common bile duct               |
| [[Pancreas]]    | Exocrine (digestive enzymes) + endocrine (insulin, glucagon) | Pancreatic duct (Wirsung) → ampulla of Vater |

## 🔑 Peritoneum & Mesenteries → [[Peritoneum]]
Most GI organs are covered by peritoneum. Mesenteries carry vessels and nerves to mobile organs. Retroperitoneal organs (duodenum, ascending/descending colon, [[Pancreas]], kidneys) are fixed.

## 🔑 Embryological Divisions & Blood Supply (Key Exam Topic)
- **Foregut** (mouth → proximal duodenum + liver, gallbladder, pancreas) → **[[Celiac Trunk]]**
- **Midgut** (distal duodenum → proximal 2/3 transverse colon) → **Superior mesenteric artery (SMA)**
- **Hindgut** (distal 1/3 transverse colon → upper anal canal) → **Inferior mesenteric artery (IMA)**

## 🏥 Clinical Significance
- **Upper GI bleed** — haematemesis / melaena; causes: peptic ulcer, varices, Mallory-Weiss tear
- **Lower GI bleed** — haematochezia; causes: diverticulosis, colorectal cancer, IBD, haemorrhoids
- **Bowel obstruction** — small (adhesions, hernia) vs. large (cancer, volvulus)
- **Peritonitis** — peritoneal inflammation → surgical emergency

